{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.103",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 103,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 103 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:1",
      "text": "Bless the Lord, O my soul; and all that is within me, bless his holy name!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:2",
      "text": "Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:3",
      "text": "who forgives all your iniquity, who heals all your diseases,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:4",
      "text": "who redeems your life from the Pit, who crowns you with steadfast love and mercy,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:5",
      "text": "who satisfies you with good as long as you live so that your youth is renewed like the eagle's.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:6",
      "text": "The Lord works vindication and justice for all who are oppressed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:7",
      "text": "He made known his ways to Moses, his acts to the people of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:8",
      "text": "The Lord is merciful and gracious, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:9",
      "text": "He will not always chide, nor will he keep his anger for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:10",
      "text": "He does not deal with us according to our sins, nor requite us according to our iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:11",
      "text": "For as the heavens are high above the earth, so great is his steadfast love toward those who fear him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:12",
      "text": "as far as the east is from the west, so far does he remove our transgressions from us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:13",
      "text": "As a father pities his children, so the Lord pities those who fear him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:14",
      "text": "For he knows our frame; he remembers that we are dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:15",
      "text": "As for man, his days are like grass; he flourishes like a flower of the field;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:16",
      "text": "for the wind passes over it, and it is gone, and its place knows it no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:17",
      "text": "But the steadfast love of the Lord is from everlasting to everlasting upon those who fear him, and his righteousness to children's children,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:18",
      "text": "to those who keep his covenant and remember to do his commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:19",
      "text": "The Lord has established his throne in the heavens, and his kingdom rules over all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:20",
      "text": "Bless the Lord, O you his angels, you mighty ones who do his word, hearkening to the voice of his word!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:21",
      "text": "Bless the Lord, all his hosts, his ministers that do his will!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.103.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 103,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 103:22",
      "text": "Bless the Lord, all his works, in all places of his dominion. Bless the Lord, O my soul!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
